Replace PATH_TO with your correct path for those directories.

1) Init DB with signals:

   $ cd vehicle_signal_interface/
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=src build/src/importVSS /PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_manager/signal_number_maps/samples.vsi

2) Enter to the vehicle_signal_manager dir:

  $ cd vehicle_signal_manager/

3) Add signals to group:

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_add_signals.py

4) Run sender:

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_vsi_sender.py

5) Run receiver:

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_vsi_receiver.py


*** Now using wait:

1) Restart DB to make sure we test with a clean environment:

   $ rm /var/run/shm/vsi*
   $ cd vehicle_signal_interface/
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=src build/src/importVSS /PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_manager/signal_number_maps/samples.vsi

2) Enter to the vehicle_signal_manager dir:

  $ cd vehicle_signal_manager/

3) Add signals to group:

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_add_signals.py

4) Run the receiver with '--wait':

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_vsi_receiver.py --wait

5) In another terminal, run the sender:

   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/src/ PYTHONPATH=/PATH_TO/vehicle_signal_interface/build/python-interfaces/ ./test_vsi_sender.py